    <h3> ABOUT US</h3>
    &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<img style="vertical-align: middle;" src="aboutus.jpg" alt="Not Found" align="middle" height="500"/>
    <p>
        UMC is North Carolina’s urban research university. It leverages its location in the state’s largest city to offer internationally competitive programs of research and creative activity, exemplary undergraduate, graduate, and professional programs, and a focused set of community engagement initiatives. UMC maintains a particular commitment to addressing the cultural, economic, educational, environmental, health, and social needs of the greater Charlotte region. <br>
        A major research university in the heart of one of the world's greatest cities, UMC provides a world-class education for its students. We are committed to creating and disseminating new knowledge as a university of growing national and international stature.<br>
        The largest university in the Charlotte area, UMC has 27,580 students, 15 colleges and annual research expenditures exceeding $335 million.A truly global institution, more than a third of UMC students speak English as a second language. UMC's student body-approximately 61 percent undergraduate and 39 percent graduate and professional-is recognized as one of the nation's most diverse. We consider this one of our greatest strengths.
